fields.description: The friendly name of the application for which the event occurred. Possible values are: outlook.exe, excel.exe. Supports: $select, $OrderBy. Read-only.
fields.name: AppDisplayName

fields.description: The publisher of the application. Supports: $select, $OrderBy. Read-only.
fields.name: AppPublisher

fields.description: The version of the application. Possible values are: 1.0.0.1, 75.65.23.9. Supports: $select, $OrderBy. Read-only.
fields.name: AppVersion

fields.description: The name of the device. Supports: $select, $OrderBy. Read-only.
fields.name: DeviceDisplayName

fields.description: The Intune device id of the device. Supports: $select, $OrderBy. Read-only.
fields.name: DeviceId

fields.description: The time the event occurred. The value cannot be modified and is automatically populated when the statistics are computed. The Timestamp type represents date and time information using ISO 8601 format and is always in UTC time. For example, midnight UTC on Jan 1, 2022 would look like this: '2022-01-01T00:00:00Z'. Returned by default. Read-only.
fields.name: EventDateTime

fields.description: The type of the event. Supports: $select, $OrderBy. Read-only.
fields.name: EventType
